        <headline>Flood Advisory issued May 13 at 7:24PM EDT until May 13 at 8:15PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...Portions of central, south central, southwest, and west
central Virginia, including the following counties and independent
cities, in central Virginia, Amherst, Appomattox, Campbell and
City of Lynchburg. In south central Virginia, Bedford. In
southwest Virginia, Craig. In west central Virginia, Alleghany VA,
Bath, Botetourt, City of Buena Vista, City of Covington, City of
Lexington and Rockbridge.

* WHEN...Until 815 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
River or stream flows are elevated.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 711 PM EDT, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges
indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Minor flooding is
ongoing with some streams near or exceeding bankfull. Between
1 and 3 inches of rain have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts of up to 1 inch are possible this
evening.  This additional rain may result in additional
flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Lynchburg...                       Lexington...
Buena Vista...                     Bedford...
Covington...                       Clifton Forge...
Amherst...
- As of 7:00 PM, Back creek in northwest Bath county is nearing
bankfull. Dunlap Creek in Alleghany county is experiencing
minor flooding. Buffalo Creek in Botetourt County is near
bankfull. Horsely Creek in Amherst county is running high,
and there has been a significant rise on the James River at
Buchanan.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.

Stay away or be swept away. River banks and culverts can become
unstable and unsafe.</instruction>
